summary: This document is a series of U.S. Department of Justice Office of the Inspector General evidence disposition forms. The forms record the authorized return or destruction of evidence items, some of which are described as containing contraband, cell phones, and other materials. The forms are partially filled out with signatures and case numbers, indicating procedural handling of evidence.

persons.name: Carl P1- 161
persons.context: Appears as the name of an authorizing official (AUSA) on one of the evidence disposition forms.

keyFacts: The document consists of multiple DOJ OIG evidence disposition forms (EFTA00123403 through EFTA00123408).
The forms document the ordered return or destruction of evidence, with descriptions including terms like 'contraband', 'cell phones', and item numbers (e.g., 1830, 1831, 1832).
One form lists 'Carl P1- 161' as an Authorizing Official, specifically an AUSA (Assistant United States Attorney).
The forms include fields for signatures of special agents, recipients, and witnesses, but most are partially illegible or incomplete in the provided text.
The standard form used is OIG FORM III - 234/4, dated 02/13/09.
